WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.060 --> 00:00:04.320
TikTok: the controversial dopamine
addiction app known for silly dances,

00:00:04.320 --> 00:00:07.740
absurdist humor, and five-star
world-class education.

00:00:07.740 --> 00:00:11.520
You can learn languages, recipes,
home improvement, crafting skills...

00:00:11.520 --> 00:00:13.680
...medical advice?

00:00:13.680 --> 00:00:14.700
History?

00:00:14.700 --> 00:00:19.140
Yeah, it shouldn't come as a surprise
that an app driven by punchy, short-form

00:00:19.140 --> 00:00:25.380
video content is a prime environment
to foster, uh, less than ideal academic integrity.

00:00:25.380 --> 00:00:28.560
Usually, you'll just get some
lightly misinformed videos,

00:00:28.560 --> 00:00:31.440
or confused people with,
like, maybe 200 views,

00:00:31.440 --> 00:00:35.220
but in some of the worst cases,
you end up with accounts touting videos

00:00:35.220 --> 00:00:39.480
with millions of views that have
unsourced, extremely questionable history;

00:00:39.480 --> 00:00:45.600
or, just as bad, try to explain extremely
complex historical concepts in one minute,

00:00:45.600 --> 00:00:49.860
that would actually take a mega long
video essay or even a book to cover.

00:00:49.860 --> 00:00:52.620
This is kind of the beef that
I personally have with

00:00:52.620 --> 00:00:54.780
some queer history education
on TikTok and Twitter.

00:00:54.780 --> 00:00:58.320
I think some folks manage
to do it well, but a lot of the time

00:00:58.320 --> 00:01:02.040
it's not a topic that can be simplified
or explained in one to three minutes

00:01:02.040 --> 00:01:06.120
or a few tweets without losing
some really valuable context.

00:01:06.120 --> 00:01:10.920
And even with the good accounts,
there usually aren't sources cited.

00:01:10.920 --> 00:01:15.840
But then there's some "history education"
accounts out there that are so bad,

00:01:15.840 --> 00:01:19.380
it's actually harmful to a&nbsp;
greater perception of the past.

00:01:19.380 --> 00:01:23.160
From the claim that people
pooped on the floor of Versailles,

00:01:23.160 --> 00:01:26.280
to the conspiracy that ancient Rome wasn't real,

00:01:26.280 --> 00:01:30.840
let's talk about TikTok and its
cesspool of historical misinformation.

